{"key":"post-6058579","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>6058579</id>\n<content>No, I've never tried recycling the grains.&amp;nbsp; I bang the jar against a tire to break up the contents, then pour them into a bowl to separate the rocks from the grains by hand.&amp;nbsp; I never figured they'd have a chance to flush again.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Actually, the above petri dishes were multispore inoculation with one or two drops right from a syringe.&amp;nbsp; That's why the growths are spread out all over the dish instead of starting only in the center.&amp;nbsp; I add just a bit of coffee(10%) to the agar to stimulate sclerotia formation, then pick some of the earliest forming stones and transfer them to grains.&amp;nbsp; This is a great way to get super producing strains.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;I prefer sclerotia to cubes, hands down.&amp;nbsp; However, I only indulge once or twice per year these days.&amp;nbsp; I prefer 50 or more fresh grams, which is only a chunk in your hand, very easy to eat.&amp;nbsp; I like the clear headed trip and the ability to actually talk if necessary.&amp;nbsp; In fact, I can almost get a whole sentence out without slurring the words, which is impossible on cubes. &lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/smileys/laugh.gif&quot; alt=&quot;:laugh:&quot; title=&quot;:laugh:&quot;/&gt;&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>6058677</next>\n<prev>6058501</prev>\n<first>6057785</first>\n<last>17520454</last>\n<when>1158199537</when>\n<utime>09/14/06 05:05 AM</utime>\n</post>"}